items.name: Tortillas & Flat Bread 365 Whole Wheat Naan
items.details: Everyday value. An authentic Indian recipe. 100% Whole Grain: 26 g or more per serving. Eat 48 g or more of whole grains daily - WholeGrainsCouncil.org. Hand-stretched and baking in a tandoor oven, our Original Naan is a wholesome version of this tender, delicious Indian flatbread. Brushed with olive oil and warmed, naan is the perfect accompaniment to any meal. But with its versatile shape and consistency, naan also has dozens of other delightful uses: Wraps - Roll naan around your favorite sandwich ingredients for a quick, easy and portable lunch. A variety of different naan wraps cut into small diagonal slices makes a beautiful party tray; Soups & Salads - For a crisp, delicious alternative to soup or salad croutons, seasoned naan with your favorite herbs and spices, cut into strips, and toast. Toasted naan strips are also a wonderful alternative to chips for dips and snacks; Pizza - Spread with pesto, sun-dried tomatoes, fresh mozzarella, and baked in the oven, naan makes a quick, light, super-easy alternative pizza base. Have fun experimenting with your own favorite toppings! www.wholefoodsmarket.com. Vegetarian. High fiber (Contains 7 g fat per serving). Product of Canada.
items.directions: Preparation: Do not reheat naan once warmed. Oven: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Remove all packaging. Place naan on a baking sheet on the middle rack of the oven. Brush naan lightly with water or olive oil. Heat for 2 minutes or until hot. Grill: Preheat grill to medium. Remove all packaging and place naan directly onto the grill. Brush naan lightly with water or olive oil. Grill for 2-3 minutes, turning once, until hot. Stovetop: Set heat to medium. Remove all packaging and place naan in pan. Brush naan lightly with water or olive oil. Heat for 2-3 minutes, turning once, until hot. Microwave: Not recommended. Naan may be frozen or stored at room temperature. Use within 5 days of defrosting/opening. Keep packaged until ready to use.
items.warnings: Contains wheat, milk and soy ingredients. May contain traces of tree nuts. Produced in a facility that processes eggs.

Tortillas & Flat Bread Sonoma Organic Traditional Wraps
items.details: 6 Artisan wraps. USDA Organic. Artisan organic wraps made with extra virgin olive oil. Committed to sustainable practices. For healthy lifestyles. 0 g Trans fat per 67 g serving size. No hydrogenated oils. Known for its pristine beauty, rich soil, pure water, mystical fog and golden coastal foothills, Sonoma County is the perfect place that inspires creation of foods that are pure, healthy and remarkable in taste. It is here, in beautiful Sonoma County that the Tamayo Family has dedicated themselves to baking the best tasting, healthy wraps and tortillas. To honor and respect this bountiful land, the Tamayo Family have now created the Sonoma line of organic and all natural wraps and tortillas, made with the finest organic and natural ingredients to ensure that each meal or snack is a unique and satisfying experience. The extra virgin olive oil advantage: Extra virgin olive oil has no trans fat and contains mono-saturated fats that are proven to reduce coronary heart disease and LDI (bad cholesterol). The organic extra virgin olive oil in Sonoma wraps and tortillas is rich in antioxidants and polyphenols that fight free radical damage in body cell caused by pollution, poor diet, stress and injury. The mono-unsaturated fats provide essential fatty acids which support the body's immune system and promote good health. Certified organic by Quality Assurance International.
items.directions: Refrigerate after purchase. May be frozen. Heat and serve. Microwave: Place one tortilla in the microwave for 20 - 25 seconds at High or until warm. (Microwave instructions suggested for 625 - 700 watt microwave). Caution: Do not use this bag in microwave. Skillet or Griddle Method: To warm and soften, place tortillas one at a time in a Medium Hot ungreased skillet. Heat each side 10 - 15 seconds until warm and soft.
